        <updateDate>2021-07-09T16:17:40Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Delivering Envelopes Judiciously On-time Year-round Act or the DEJOY Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the U.S. Postal Service (USPS) to maintain the service standards for first-class mail that were in effect on January 1, 2021. The Postmaster General proposed in March 2021 a 10-year restructuring plan for the USPS that would lengthen the permissible mail-delivery window. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
